..TEXT:
|Poi, come 'l foco... dura~: See the following in
the passage from Thomas Aquinas quoted in the preceding note:
"sicut ignis ex sua forma inclinatur ad superiorem locum."  The
place to which fire rises is the elemental circle of fire which
was thought to lie inside and nearest to the sphere of the moon.
A flame seeks to rise to that, as to its proper place.  Cf.
^Par.~ I, 115.  "Nata" here clearly implies natural love.
..TEXT:
|movesi~ = ^si move.~
