..TEXT:
|e mai non posa... gioire~: Aquinas' statement of
the third and last stage of love is: "Et ultimo quies, quae est
gaudium" (see quotation from the ^Summa theologica~ in n. to vs.
23). "Posa" here corresponds to the "quies" of Aquinas, and
"gioire" to "gaudium," by which we see that the poet has followed
exactly the accepted presentation of the operation of love.  At
the third stage the circle of love is complete, as Aquinas,
following closely his Aristotle, observes (see the quotation in
the preceding note).  The end of the movement is possession and
fruition of the object.  |il~ = ^lo.~
