..TEXT:
|e l'anima non va con altro piede~: This is the
lesson of the preceding canto and the central lesson of the whole
poem: all movements of the soul are to be seen as movements of
love and "neither Creator nor any creature... was ever without
love" as ^Purg.~ XVII, 91-92, states it.  For the metaphor of the
foot, or feet, of the soul, see n. to ^Inf.~ I, 30.
