..TEXT:
|Quanto ragion qui vede, dir ti poss'io~: Virgil
here declares that he speaks within the limits of reason or
philosophy (see reference to the philosophers in vs. 67), as
distinct from theology or Christian revelation.  Thus he carries
his argument as far as he can within the declared range of
natural reason, then refers it on to Beatrice.
