|accoglie e viglia~: See n. to vs. 63 and the second
passage from Gregory quoted there, with its notion of winnowing.
Each of the two verbs would seem to look in a different direction
from the "threshold of assent," with "accoglie" denoting a
receiving from without and "viglia" a winnowing of impulses
within as they move outward toward the object of desire.  Cf.
"ritener" in vs. 72.     |viglia~ = ^vaglia.~
