|poniam che... s'accende~: "Poniam che" means
"let us grant that," i.e., let it be granted for purposes of the
argument that... (cf. Marco Lombardo's similar concession in
^Purg.~ XVI, 74).  What Virgil says must be granted, of course,
since the soul "ad ogne cosa @e mobile che piace" (vs. 20).
