|Pietola~: Pronounced ^Pi@etola.~  This village, now
known as Pietole, is about three miles south of Mantua and is
commonly identified with the ancient Andes, the birthplace of
Virgil.     |pi@u che villa mantoana~: The words lend themselves
to two possible interpretations: more famous than any other
Mantuan town; or more famous than Mantua itself.  The first seems
preferable.
