..TEXT:
|E quale Ismeno... uopo~: "Quale" modifies "furia
e calca" ("such a rush and crowd as").  The reference is to the
famous Bacchic orgies, invoking the god.  Ismenus and Asopus are
small rivers of Boeotia; the first flows through Thebes, the
second near the city.  According to tradition Thebes was the
birthplace of Bacchus, whose mother, Semele, was a Theban.
..TEXT:
|pur che~: Literally, "if only."
