..TEXT:
|non vi bugio~ = ^non vi dico bugia.~  See E. G.
Parodi (1957), pp. 264, 374.  Virgil's declaration here to these
souls that Dante is alive becomes all the more emphatic for this
touch, but these souls, driven by just love and good will, have
no time to marvel over the fact that Dante is alive, as do souls
in other circles.
