..TEXT:
|Io fui abate in San Zeno a Verona~: Nothing is
actually known of this abbot, though he has been identified with
a certain Gherardo II, who was abbot of the church of San Zeno in
Verona in the time of the Emperor Frederick I and who died in
1187.  The famous church and cloister of San Zeno (Zeno was
bishop of Verona in the fourth century), which are very old, are
but a short distance outside the old city.
