..TEXT:
|del buon Barbarossa~: Cf. the similar reference to
Augustus in ^Inf.~ I, 71.  The term means merely "worthy."  Thus
Benvenuto says: "Vocat Fridericum bonum, quia fuit vir virtuosus,
strenuus, largus triumphator et corpore pulcer."  ("He calls
Frederick good, because he was a man of virtue, strong, a great
conqueror, and very handsome of body.")
..TCHR:
